      • getClassesGen

        @NotNull
public IFile getClassesGen()
        Specified by:
        getClassesGen in interface JavaModuleFacet
        Returns:
        root folder where generated classes of any module's model reside, or null if associated module doesn't expect class files to be written. Note, although generated classes are part of classpath, this method is to access design-time location of generated classes, not that at deployment time. For deployed modules, this method may return null, while generated module classes would be available for classloading through JavaModuleFacet.getClassPath().
